{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048179,"nonce":"47ojqoWk1xFEkEXclGuj7crFImA=","title":"Add vector-style edge routing tools","message":"[Imported from GitHub #48] (created 2026-01-30T05:09:52Z)\n\n## Problem\nThe canvas only supports auto-routed curves, and the current elbow UI is not a full\nvector-style routing workflow. Users need to place elbows or spline control points\nwhile drawing, and have that layout persist as part of the graph UI state.\n\n## Context\nWe want both a simple mode (auto routing) and an explicit mode (manual elbows or\nsplines) with clear affordances. Layout should be stored with edges and reloaded\nfaithfully.\n\n## Potential Solutions\n- Add drawing modes: auto (bezier) and manual (polyline/spline)\n- Allow click-to-add elbows during edge creation; double-click to finish\n- Store routing points in edge UI state and render them consistently\n- Provide a compact toolbar with icon affordances and keyboard modifiers\n\n## Related Opportunities\nPoint editing could also power annotation connectors or layout guides elsewhere in\nthe UI for callouts/analysis overlays.\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: Codex (GPT-5) \u003ccodex@openai.com\u003e","files":null}]}